<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,326,786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,507,533]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">Remarks:</emphasis>
The geographically closest record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marktanner-Turneretscher" authorityYear="1887" box="[741,880,507,534]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="foveolata">
<emphasis box="[741,761,508,534]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[776,880,507,533]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">foveolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
previously reported was from northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,507,533]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[159,292,543,569]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" refId="ref17104" refString="OBIS (2019) OBIS. Ocean Biogeographic Information system. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO. Available from: http: // www. iobis. org (accessed 17 May 2019)" type="url" year="2019">OBIS 2019</bibRefCitation>
), which suggests that our find extends its distribution northwards. This species is characterized by its distinct color pattern. The radial shields are demarcated by a dark purple line, the arms are banded in yellow, white and rose-purple, separated by thin dark purple bands. Our specimens showed faint dark purple dots in the center of each dorsal arm plate, which in one specimen are rings with lighter center rather than dots, the arm spines are a faded pink. This concurs with the description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler, R." box="[729,905,687,713]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 486" refId="ref15740" refString="Koehler, R. (1922) Ophiurans of the Philippine Seas and adjacent waters. Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin, 100, 1 - 486." type="journal article" year="1922">Koehler (1922)</bibRefCitation>
. It is a smaller species, with disc diameter less than 
<quantity box="[206,285,723,750]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
and arms about six times as long as the disc diameter (Koehler 1905, 1922). This also concurs with our specimens. The 
<typeStatus box="[332,380,760,786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
locality is Aru Islands in 
<collectingCountry box="[668,777,759,785]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marktanner-Turneretscher, G." box="[791,1154,759,785]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" pagination="291 - 316" refId="ref16461" refString="Marktanner-Turneretscher, G. (1887) Beschreibung neuer Ophiuriden und Bemerkungen zu bekannten. Annalen des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 2, 291 - 316. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 29076" type="journal article" year="1887">Marktanner-Turneretscher 1887</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
